         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Edition from SEG 42, 885.</p>
            <p>1. - - -οι: nominative plural of an ethnikon, Β. 2. or ἀτ]έλειαν, Β. 2-3.
                    ἔν|[κτασιν γᾶς], previous scholars 3. καὶ], Β., who interprets γάμορος/γάμοροι
                    as the citizen-body of landowners rather than as the small elite of aristocratic
                    estate-owners; B. interprets γαμόρον as genitive plural: ‘if he becomes one of
                    the γάμοροι’ 4. restored by B. up to ἀ]ρχᾶν.</p>
